<PRE>
Date: Wed, 13 Dec 1995 09:20:45 +0000 ()
From: Brandon Gillespie &lt;brandon@tombstone.sunrem.com&gt;
To: coldstuff@tombstone.sunrem.com

All of the file functions will hook through the new file handling system 
I have hacked up.  It will basically only work with a chunk of the file 
at a time, to keep it from blocking up tasks.  Right now the block 
defaults to 512 bytes (or something around there).  It is setable on the 
fly.  All file functions should be secured when running in a virtual 
environment.

-Brandon Gillespie-
